Doc Spatz:<br><br>
Drugs, the perpetual problem that labels the Vietnam Veteran. I did not use drugs in Vietnam, but I understand the emotional problems that drove many to that magic bullet of escape from the pain of it all. The legally sanctioned addictive behavior of alcoholism was, in my estimation, a far more perverse problem. Addictive behavior with sex and killing were used, too, as ways of momentary relief from the pain at the core of one's being.<br><br>
Like repression, none of it really worked, ever. These are now severe issues of corrosive baggage for many still caught in the teeth of the emotional meat grinder of the Vietnam Experience.<br><br>
I agree we need to discuss this.
